    "description": "Handcrafted fixture for test_ability.py — simulates a sub-2:50 marathon trainee's two-week training block ending 2026-04-23.",
    "design_notes": [
      "HR-pace regression line is intentionally collinear (slope -1, intercept 465) so A1.3 (append collinear easy run) preserves the secondary VO2max regression exactly.",
      "Baseline activities have no per-km laps, so neither the Daniels rep-summation path nor race-like path of compute_l3_vo2max fires. This keeps vo2max_primary = 0 at baseline, letting A1.4's new 6x1K set primary for the first time.",
      "A1.4's pace is 3:45/km (not the plan's literal 5:20/km) because a 5:20/km 6x1K is physically incompatible with 'marathon_estimate_s decreased' for a sub-2:50 target: it yields VDOT ~36, lower than baseline secondary VDOT ~46, so source would flip to primary AND marathon estimate would regress. 3:45/km yields VDOT ~54, clearly above secondary floor.",
      "Recovery RHR baseline median = 48 bpm. Uth-Sorensen floor ≈ 15.3*185/48 ≈ 59. Still below primary A1.4 VDOT (~54)? No wait: 59>54 so source priority would NOT pick primary over floor... let's re-read ability.py: priority is primary>secondary>floor. As long as primary>0, primary wins regardless of magnitude. ✓",
      "Activity dates use ISO strings with UTC offset so ability.py's Shanghai-local-time filter treats them as the intended day."
    ]
  },
